Police have launched a major crackdown on illegal fuel dealers and recovered nearly 200,000 litres of adulterated petroleum in Nakuru and Eldoret.In one of the operations, General Service Unit officers found 62,000 litres of fuel in Kibunja forest, Koibatek in Molo Sub-County.Two suspects were also arrested and are expected in court Friday.During the 6pm raid on Thursday, police also impounded three lorries, seven generators, solar batteries 16 drums, metallic seals, 11 tanks and hosepipes.The yard was once used by a Chinese construction company before abandoning it.Police are looking for a businessman believed to be the owner of the yard.In Eldoret, Uasin Gishu County, police conducted a similar operation at Jua Kali at around 1.30 pm Thursday.The officers were accompanied by a team from the Energy and Regulation Commission.The fuel was hidden in underground tanks.Two lorries, pumped and generators were also impounded during the operation. email print email print Job boycott should be suspended to allow room for talks this week, judge rules. There are 32 million chicken in the country that are at risk of contracting the avian flu.